<br>
On a personal note, I left Karana because I found it difficult (due to lag) to operate on Karana with constant 2000+ pop counts during my 'prime' time.  I didn't care to sign on at 8AM on Saturday morning (US Central) and find 1800+ people already going at it, with a pop count of 2600+ by 5PM.  I neither loved nor hated the KGC, despite it's flaws.  It was simply the system in place I worked with on behalf of my guild.  Since I left my guild to move, they are now trying to find their own way to work with the KGC.<br>
<br>
My point with this post is to say that while we (from Karana) understand your frustration at dealing with a reservation system booked months in advance, it's not somthing we had to deal with.  I wouldn't care for a system like that and I know those groups who hated the KGC would absolutely detest such an arrangement.  I've seen a number of proposals presented here to help everyone ease their transition to Ay Ro.  The reality of the matter is no one is going to set up any sort of sharing system until it is proven one is necessary.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> If</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> this happens it will only be after a couple months have gone by, as you have rightly pointed out Fandariella.  Until then, people will need to be patient and allow the situation to sort itself out. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Unguilded&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usorchastormseeker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorcha Stormseeker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/28/00 6:58:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=83>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conesus--- FFA planes or schedule</span><hr size=1> Well spoken Jzonn.  Allied Giants left Karana because of the over crowding and lag issues for the most part.  We did well working with the KGC.  Those in the Forged Alliance worked within the KGC and all went well.  To come from that type of environment into a FFA and somewhat worrisome look at certain guilds just jumping in and taking a plane that you are camping...its scary to say the least.  Some have balked at the thought of going to the planes for anything other then to take down the Gods.  That in and of itself amazes me...&lt;one who stands before you in only 50% planes gear&gt;.  I think that FFA could work.  I also have noticed the past few nites no one has been in Hate.  Which of course had me drooling...thinking of all those free range Kira's running around with MY BREASTPLATE!!!!!!!! &lt;regains control of herself&gt;.  <br>
<br>
There are many different views on the subject of rotation, scheduling and planning.  If we all take time and consider everyones views and concerns then I think we can all come to an equitable solution.  Hopefully any preconcieved ideas about **UBER GUILDS** and their good/bad reps can be overriden.  I, for the most part haven't seen anything too horrible yet on the boards or on the server.  I would hope that possibly those that had the bad reps might be looking for a bit of atonement here in Ayonae Ro.  &lt;weeps...Clerics bless us One and All!!!....passes tissues around&gt;<br>
