 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umochaboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MochaBoy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/28/00 4:47:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://64.37.109.125/everquest/sig2.jpg height=163 width=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conesus--- FFA planes or schedule</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What is Karana like these days? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Interesting question - and I'd been waiting for the chance to chime in.<br>
<br>
1st order of business - Hi to all my old friends (Jzonn, Halagar, Hoo?, Chia, Sapula, Monza, Katori, that dancing Gnecro etc...etc...I'm sure I left folks out)that left Karana for greener pastures on ARo.  I like what I've been seeing so far after studying your messages boards for the past few days.  It looks like [bold]for the most part[/bold] you've got a server with very mature and competent players that know precisely the situation they're in and the powder keg they're sitting on.  Rather than light the fuse - I see so many instances of folks _WANTING_ to work together and doing just that - absolutely warms the heart :)<br>
<br>
But you guys are sorely missed - and with the holidays upon us - there seems to be this calm stillness about the server - not much going on in the ways of activity.<br>
<br>
As far as the server's concerned:<br>
- Remf is organizing an Evil Only raid on the PoG and is getting amazing buy in.  I unfortunately will be the only paladin on duty to protect Tunare's plane from their invasion.  I just bought a shiny new STOP sign and plan on putting it to use during their raid, but I'm skeptical of its utility.<br>
<br>
- Vox is down to 4 guilds in the rotation - Nag's pretty much steady, VS and Cazic are still on decent rotations - but with everyone having left - there were a few raids that went kaput because there weren't enough folks on to take him at the time.  Everything seems a little sedate on Karana now - Lower Guk fluctuates from between 15 and 30 people but I have yet to see it over 35.  Cougars are being slaughtered by hundreds of thousands in the EW by PBAE groups harvesting them for their earrings.  <br>
<br>
There's some fancy shmansy new 8ac 8str 8mr +8DS quest ring that folks just started getting wind of (starts in Eastern Waste with a dorf I thunk).  Paladins are crying foul because our Runed Protector's armor has boobs instead of pecs, and the greaves look like some shiny leotard reject from a bad production of River Dance.<br>
<br>
The KCoG has gone into a little bit of a hibernation mode because of all the guilds that were affected - the medium sized guilds were affected the most.  Up and Coming guilds with 30 members, saw all of their high level folks leaving for ARo and it's thrown that scene into a little bit of an uproar.  Alliance have come apart because they're one third the size they were pre split.  There's some stabilization and consolidation that needs to happen with the mid to small size guilds and the smart ones are joining forces through mergers or alliances.  <br>
<br>
But that aside - Pippi is still conducting her Large Target Raid Symposium set for sometime in January - and I think she's still forging ahead with the Server Wide Chess Tournament.<br>
<br>
As for me and the daggers :)  Well we just got our first cleric to 39 (yay), got about 6 planes capable members, our mid level teams are learning how to run raids now (yay), I finally got my shrunken Goblin Earring and Bracer of the Hidden so I've been going around casting on everyone in sight, and I led my first successful raid (zero deaths, buffed and broke in in 43 minutes) against the Golden Efreeti (we're up to 5 boots for the alliance now :).<br>
<br>
(ps sorry for the zigging and zagging)<br>
<br>
Oh and as for FFA vs Rotation?<br>
<br>
You guys have an ENORMOUS concentration of high level players on your server.  BUT, it also seems like those players are all mature individuals who still remember their kindergarten teacher's lessons on sharing.  I like the way you guys are announcing your intentions and then falling back on diplomacy to work things out if 2 groups want to be up there.  I also think for that to be a success there is only ONE RULE you guys need to follow.<br>
<br>
Learn to Limit Yourselves.<br>
<br>
If the guild leaders can espouse that ideological paradigm, I can't possibly see how things can go wrong.  We have the KGC and KCoG so we don't HAVE to worry about trusting whether or not people will adhere to the rules - the system in place simply won't give them the opportunity.  Without it - there will eventually come that one group who believes wholeheartedly that might makes right and they can singlehandedly destroy the peace on a server.  I've read consistent accounts of some of the uber guilds on your server now and if they don't learn to limit themselves, things are going to get out of hand.<br>
<br>
Uber guilds are self perpetuating entities that grow and grow and the more they grow - the more they need to be fed, until the point where that desire outstrips the environment's ability to supply it without sacrificing everyone and everything else around it.<br>
<br>
but that's all speculation...  :)<br>
<br>
So good luck guys - pop in every now and again and let us know how you're doing - god knows our server has been stripped of some of its best qualities.<br>
<br>
<br>
Shoji Tsunami<br>
