<br>
We encountered two other guilds in the zone while we were there: Landslide and Undead Lords.  I'd like to comment on the FFA type system based on our experiences with these two other &quot;competing&quot; guilds.<br>
<br>
First, Landslide was courteous and receptive.  Ranina and I spoke early on and attempted to work out a means of sharing the zone; unfortunately the zone stayed very empty a lot.  We even discussed the possibility of jointly taking down Maestro, however, Landslide wanted to try, and we originally had no intention of trying, so wished them luck.  All in all, not a bad experience.<br>
<br>
Second, our experiences with Undead Lords were mixed.  The first day, we had a number of incidents of &quot;clashing heads&quot; in that the zone was pretty empty, so we ended up competing over any mob that spawned.  Words were exchanged and bad feelings started.  The second day, UL seemed more open to trying to share with us, and we even ended up sharing drops that neither group needed.<br>
<br>
My conclusion:  FFA will not work on this server.  I can imagine how it would have been if a third guild decided to join in on that last day.  Everyone would have been all over each other.  <br>
<br>
Therefore, I suggest from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> AyRo experience</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> now that we need a method of, not necessarily scheduling, but of at least announcing intents.  And, other guilds need to realize that a posted intent has to be able to carry some weight.  If guilds are going to do as they wish with as many people capable of doing these types of situations as AyRo has, then we *NEED* a means of working ALL together, not against each other, or we'll all end up fighting constantly. <p><img src="http://www.concentric.net/~purgon/gilpaint.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usinadilye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinadilye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/1/01 6:07:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=89>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conesus--- FFA planes or schedule</span><hr size=1> What about the people who don't read these boards?<br>
