PREFACE: This post isn't directed at Strike, but his post does serve as an excellent starting point for my comments and questions.<br>
<br>
I don't think people really have a problem when there isn't any contention.  The question becomes, what happens when two (or more) groups 'need' the same spawn in a plane which is in a farming mode (as will be the case in those few months you mentioned)?  Who is to say who's need is greater?  Is it based on the highest level there?  Is it based on the number of a particular class present who could use the drop (assuming a drop occurs)?<br>
<br>
As Palimax has rightly stated, we are in a state of FFA because some guilds wish it.  I don't have a problem with that at all.  I think most guilds either don't have a problem with it or recognize they will need to deal with the situation (make the best of it).  This doesn't just apply to the planes as a whole, but the individual mobs within the planes (taking the PNP into account, of course).  Unless you have specifically received a promise to leave all the spawns of a_plane_mob00 alone from the other group(s) up there with you, don't expect those mobs to be uncontested.<br>
<br>
If a group consistently pulls more (or all) of these (re)spawns, don't get mad.  Learn how they are doing it.  Pulling is an art and master pullers are true artisans.  It may take some time to gain an equal footing with them, but in the end you'll be able to hold your own.  This isn't a sprint or even a marathon.  It's a path you'll need to follow to reach a goal.  Recognize there will be obstacles and work to eliminate them. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Unguilded&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
