<br>
This really depends on what you're talking about... if you're talking about Inny well then whoever gets to him first.  That's not to say some jack ass guild will be keeping tabs through people in zone and be waiting until the zone is cleared then make a mad rush at him as I've seen happen in the past on CT.  Everyone can decide from that point on how they will treat the offending guild in their future dealings with them.  If you're talking about rare epic mobs such as the book of souls... again, whoever gets to him first. If the guild who gets to it first and makes the kill requires the item, then fine, someone who needed it was present and got it.  Not many guilds have more than 5 or 6 rogues if that many.  It may take a week to get that mob.  However, that's still better than being on a 6 month waiting list still trying to get in there. If the guild making the kill doesn't need it I expect they will let the zone know so someone can come over and loot the item.  Common courtesy.  Sometimes it requires your guild to do a few clearings to get what they need such as the book of lost souls. Be persistent and be present and eventually you will get it.  However you distribute loot within your own guild is up to you.  On regular mobs, say we're primarily out for warrior drops... I don't expect to lay claim to every mummy in the zone.  You get some... we get some... if stuff drops that you need then great we're not going to haggle or fight over them.  I'd much rather someone from any guild get something instead of letting it rot.  <br>
<br>
Another issue is going to be clearing ability.  Some guilds are capable of clearing the planes in 2-3 hours.  It's taken a lot of practice and a lot of deaths to be able to achieve that.  Any guild that's achieved that ability will almost certaintly have most of the gear they need already and most drops that occur will be up for grabs to other guilds present.  When a guild like that is present it can become a time saving device for all other guilds present.  I know most everyone hates staying up to 3am in the morning trying to get a plane cleared... you can't operate for shit in real life the next day especially when clearing on weekday evenings.  Anyway, the faster the plane is cleared the sooner we can all get a respawn and we can get a higher yeild of drops out of there each week.  It all balances out.    <br>
<br>
Gildhar, I'll have a talk with the manufacturer of my video card.  Apparently, there is a problem with it.  Somehow, a female bard in gold and green armor kept running across my screen every 5 minutes that evening while I was out pulling throughout the night. Must have been a glitch or one of the most persistent zone ghosts I have ever seen.  Regardless, occurences such as this will happen, it's inevitable.  1-2 times or even 5-6 times in an evening is really nothing with that many people trying to operate in there.  I'm sure you're familiar with the old safehall/lord/frenzy camps in guk all fighting for spawns.  It's going to happen, people. Sometimes accidents just happen and no one is really to blame.  There's nothing personal involved.  No one is out to purposely deprive you of every mob in the zone.  It's best to go in there with the attitude that everything is cool so long as someone in the zone gets what's dropped and nothing rots while people present are there needing.<br>
<br>
More drops in less time = more people getting what they need in less time.<br>
<br>
A calendar is highly inefficient as drops will rot and there will be solo guilds that take an entire evening and some of the next day to get a plane cleared.  The goal for everyone should be keeping that plane cleared in the least amount of time possible.<br>
